business_analysis.business_domain: Local peer-to-peer marketplace platform enabling individuals to buy and sell used and new items within their communities
business_analysis.business_model: Transaction-based marketplace with revenue from promoted listings, seller fees, shipping services, and premium features for sellers to increase visibility
key_products_services: Mobile app for buying and selling
business_analysis.target_customers: Individual consumers looking to buy or sell used goods locally, including casual sellers decluttering homes, bargain hunters, collectors, small resellers, and vehicle/high-value item sellers

key_entities.name: users
key_entities.description: Individual buyers and sellers on the platform, with dual roles

key_entities.name: listings
key_entities.description: Items posted for sale across 15+ categories including vehicles, electronics, home goods, clothing, collectibles

key_entities.name: categories
key_entities.description: Product taxonomy including Electronics, Vehicles, Home & Garden, Clothing, Baby & Kids, Collectibles, etc.

key_entities.name: transactions
key_entities.description: Completed sales between buyers and sellers

key_entities.name: messages
key_entities.description: In-app communications between buyers and sellers

key_entities.name: locations
key_entities.description: Geographic data for local transactions (city, state, zip code)

key_entities.name: promotions
key_entities.description: Paid listing enhancements and featured placements

data_products.name: Seller Analytics Dashboard
data_products.description: Performance metrics for sellers including views, favorites, response rates, and sales

data_products.name: Listing Insights
data_products.description: Data on listing performance, optimal pricing suggestions, and category trends

data_products.name: Market Price Intelligence
data_products.description: Pricing data and trends for similar items in local markets

primary_use_cases: Marketplace health monitoring and GMV tracking
Fraud detection and trust & safety monitoring
Revenue optimization from promotions and fees
business_questions: What is our GMV trend by category and geography over time?
Which categories have the highest conversion rates and why?
What is the lifetime value of sellers by acquisition channel?
How does listing price affect time-to-sale and conversion?
What are the characteristics of our most successful sellers?
Which geographic markets show the highest growth potential?
What is the optimal pricing strategy for promoted listings?
How do seasonal trends affect different product categories?
What factors drive user retention and repeat transactions?
Which search terms have low conversion and need better inventory?
What is the fraud rate by category and user segment?
How does message response time correlate with transaction success?
What percentage of listings result in successful sales?
Which user cohorts have the highest engagement and GMV?
How do shipping vs local pickup preferences vary by category?
demo_opportunities: Build a marketplace health dashboard showing GMV, active listings, and transaction trends
Create a category performance analysis comparing conversion rates, average prices, and inventory levels
Demonstrate geographic heat mapping of market activity and growth opportunities
Show seller segmentation analysis identifying power sellers vs casual users
Build a pricing intelligence tool showing competitive pricing by category and location
Create a user retention cohort analysis tracking buyer and seller behavior over time
Demonstrate fraud detection patterns using transaction and behavioral anomalies
Build a search analytics dashboard showing query trends and conversion funnels
Show seasonal trend analysis for inventory planning and marketing
Create a listing optimization recommender based on successful listing attributes
Demonstrate real-time marketplace monitoring with alerts for key metric changes
Build a revenue attribution model for promoted listings and platform fees

additional_context.geographic_focus: US (with evidence of listings across multiple states including NE, IA, FL, VA, WA)
notable_features: Strong local/geographic focus differentiating from national marketplaces
Wide category diversity from low-value items ($10) to high-value vehicles ($69,950)
Mobile-first platform with app download emphasis
Dual-sided marketplace with users as both buyers and sellers
Trust and safety critical given peer-to-peer transactions
Shipping integration expanding beyond local-only model
High-value categories like vehicles and collectibles present significant GMV opportunity
Competitive with Craigslist, Facebook Marketplace, and Mercari
